<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-05-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-05-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="346" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d346">
                    <head>Wesleyan Ministers and Stewards of Dublin</head>
                    <dateline>94 <hi rend="smallcaps">Stephen’s Green, <placeName type="city">Dublin</placeName></hi>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-05-10">
                            <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 10, 1865</date>.</dateline>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to transmit to you the
                        accompanying resolutions, passed at a meeting of the Wesleyan ministers and
                        stewards of the Dublin district, and concurred in by the other districts in
                        Ireland, which met at the same time.</p>
                    <p>I have the honor to be, your excellency’s very obedient servant,</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>ROBERT WALLACE,</signed>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Wesleyan Minister</hi>.</closer>
                    <postscript>
                        <p>His Excellency the <hi rend="smallcaps">President</hi>
                            <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">of the United States</hi>.</p>
                    </postscript>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>